sequenceDiagram
    participant CP as Charge Point (OCTT)
    participant CS as Central System (SUT)

    Note over CP,CS: Test Case: TC_076_CSMS
    Note over CP,CS: Delete a specific certificate from the Charge Point
    Note over CP,CS: Steps 1-8 repeated for each hash algorithm (SHA256, SHA384, SHA512)

    Note over CP,CS: Phase 1: Install CentralSystemRootCertificate 2

    CS->>CP: 1. InstallCertificate.req
    Note right of CS: certificateType = CentralSystemRootCertificate<br/>certificate = CentralSystemRootCertificate 2

    CP-->>CS: 2. InstallCertificate.conf
    Note left of CP: status = Accepted

    Note over CP,CS: Phase 2: Delete the just installed certificate

    CS->>CP: 3. GetInstalledCertificateIds.req
    Note right of CS: Confirm hashAlgorithm for deletion

    CP-->>CS: 4. GetInstalledCertificateIds.conf
    Note left of CP: status = Accepted<br/>certificateHashData.hashAlgorithm = <hash alg>

    CS->>CP: 5. DeleteCertificate.req
    Note right of CS: hashAlgorithm = <from step 4><br/>certificateHashData = <installed cert info>

    CP-->>CS: 6. DeleteCertificate.conf
    Note left of CP: status = Accepted

    CS->>CP: 7. GetInstalledCertificateIds.req (optional)
    Note right of CS: Confirm certificate was deleted

    CP-->>CS: 8. GetInstalledCertificateIds.conf
